Date: Fri, 26 Jun 2026 22:17:04 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] AccessibilityAnalysis: wheelchair costing +
 config-tunable Valhalla isochrone detail
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Picks up BACKLOG §3 follow-ups.

- Wheelchair: Valhalla has no first-class wheelchair costing, so the profile
  was mapped to bare `pedestrian`. Now also send
  `costing_options: {pedestrian: {type: "wheelchair"}}` (avoids steps, honours
  `wheelchair=*` access tags) via new `toValhallaCostingOptions()`, emitted only
  for the wheelchair profile.

- Detail levers (more detailed / higher-resolution isochrones): `generalize`
  (Douglas-Peucker tolerance, metres; null/omitted = Valhalla default, 0 = max
  fidelity) and `denoise` (0..1; keep small reachable pockets) are now driven by
  a new `valhallaIsochroneOptions` state field, threaded through a new
  `isochroneOptions` arg (methodsAnalysis -> getIsochrones action ->
  createIsochrones -> requestIsochrones -> requestIsochronesValhalla).
  Defaults stay backward-compatible (generalize null, denoise 1); Valhalla-only,
  the ORS path ignores it.

- Contour-band count left at 3 (deferred): structurally baked into
  styleIsochroneFeatures %3/%4 math, getDistances/getSteps, and steps.length
  grouping; a much larger change with real per-request cost.

5 new unit tests (wheelchair options, default body, explicit levers,
generalize 0 vs null); all 13 pass, eslint clean.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
